column2:
Played this game back during the times of the beta. Had it pre-ordered and tried to follow the game through its many updates. So, I can safely say, that without a shadow of a doubt;

I can only recommend someone this game IF they were willing to put more money on the table and just buy the Legacy Collection. Any other DLCs afterwards I can't recommend since I never bought them. I think that overall, the game is fine. The gameplay loop is what's gonna keep you coming back, along with the unlockables. I'm glad that a third game is going to be released, and this game is great to play with your buds or by yourself! However, I will say this. If you just want to do some heisting, play with your pals, and don't care about unlocks?

Just go buy PAYDAY: The Heist. Its cheaper, and with only one thing of DLC.

I don't have much to say about PayDay 2 especially because I joined pretty late of its release but I see why it was so popular and controversial back then and can't say it didn't deserve its popularity.
I really like the characters,the amazing music,how you can approach missions from the brainless shoot everyone to the more tactic and rewarding stealth or how nutty some missions are [spoiler]like where you have to steal f*cking nukes[/spoiler] but [b]in my opinion[/b] it loses quite a bit without a friend or someone that knows a lot of the game because it takes a lot of time to understand it and perfectionate equip or strategy which is good aswell.Another problem is that it sort of become repetitive and boring quiet fast,this is why I try to play stealth which makes the mission more various and tedious instead of a shoot-shoot-shoot-everyone every mission but the ones I play with prefer that and for me it becomes repetitive fast,the only salvations are the laugh that I can have with my mates to break that mood.

[b]PROS:[/b]
[list]
[*] Awesome music;
[*] LOT of stuff to obtain...;
[*] Charismatic characters;
[*] Fun combat;
[*] Playable with other 4 players;
[*] Stealth gives different options to approach the mission...;
[*] Satisfying arsenal;
[*] LOT of customization...;
[*] Many missions to play...;
[*] Actual narrative that you can follow;
[*] Compatible with Steam Workshop...
[/list]

[b]CONS:[/b]
[list]
[*] Grind can be very long and tedious even just for one item\gun;
[*] ...but lot of the better stuff is behind a paywall;
[*] Some missions are only available daily;
[*] Mechanics aren't explained that much creating lot of confusion through the menus;
[*] Random players in multiplayer have the easy "kickvote",one mistake or not fast enough and you are out;
[*] ...but there isn't enough incentive to go stealth or to have fun with it;
[*] Some civilians that could randomly witness something when you less expect it or pop out from nowhere;
[*] ...but,again,lot of the customization is behind DLCs or paywalls;
[*] ...but missions don't differentiate that much from each to each most of the times;
[*] Weird choice for John Wich voice actor;
[*] ...but you can only get skins from the Workshop.

I'll give this game a [b]7.9\10[/b],I am so curious to see how they can improve from this to PayDay 2 hoping that they actually improve it and don't release a crap,broken,heavily monetized and unfinished game.

It's fucking Payday 2, do I even need to explain why it goes hard?

Or... in other words;
